race.comment: HEAVEN SPECIFIED (1) resumed at Bunbury off a try at Stakes level and was beaten a whisker after enduring a tough run. He has more to give and will enjoy a soft run from the inside barrier. He can go one better. SHE'S CAPITANA (9) debuts for the Durrant yard with the gun hoop booked. She's won her last two Lark Hill trials and jumps from an inside barrier. A bold run is on the cards. GOLDEN OPERA (4) resumes and two back she was beaten 3L in a Group 3 over this distance. Maps well and was placed in a recent Belmont trial. Has plenty of ability, and the betting will be key. CAWARRA (6) has a wide gate but deserves to be kept safe on resumption. Two back she was heavily bet in an Open 2 at Ascot on debut with Chris Parnham aboard and he rides today. She was beaten a nose in a recent Belmont trial and looks ready to go.
